article.headline: Tennessee Tech 98, Harvard 93 (OT)
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. (AP) -- Derek Stribling scored 21 points to lead Tennessee Tech to a 98-93 overtime win over Harvard on Thursday night in the third place game of the Saturn Shootout. Anthony Fisher's layup with 44 seconds remaining in overtime put the Golden Eagles (5-6) ahead for good. Fisher, who finished with 17 points, was one of six players in double figures for Tennessee Tech. Harvard missed two 3-pointers in the final 34 seconds that would have either given the Crimson (4-8) the lead or tied the game. In regulation, Harvard took the lead on one of Kevin Rogus' seven 3-pointers at the 15:37 mark of the second half. The Crimson led by five with 2:46 left, but the Golden Eagles used a 6-0 run to take the lead back, 77-76. Jenkins' free throw to put the Golden Eagles ahead 82-80 with eight seconds to go, but Matt Stehle's tip-in sent it to overtime. The Golden Eagles converted three free throws at the beginning of overtime and sealed it with three more late. Rogus led the Crimson with 27 points and Stehle added 22.
